---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Press | ExNulla">
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-8">Press & Media</h1>

    <p class="text-base text-muted mb-6">
      ExNulla is an open engineering lab documenting the construction of complex software systems in
      public.
    </p>

    <p class="text-base text-muted mb-6">
      The project was conceived, architected, and built by a single operator over a period of
      twenty-three days using a structured AI-assisted development pipeline. The ecosystem includes
      a public engineering site, interactive technical demonstrations, CI/CD pipelines,
      infrastructure automation, and a live development stream documenting the build process.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4">What ExNulla Demonstrates</h2>

    <ul class="space-y-3 text-muted">
      <li>Designing deterministic engineering systems for AI-assisted development.</li>
      <li>Operating a complete developer ecosystem as a single engineer.</li>
      <li>Building transparent proof-of-work portfolios instead of static resumes.</li>
      <li>
        Combining architecture, infrastructure, and public documentation into one operational
        system.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4">Author</h2>

    <p class="text-muted">
      James is a systems architect and operator focused on deterministic engineering systems,
      AI-assisted development workflows, and infrastructure-driven software architecture.
    </p>

    <p class="text-muted mt-4">
      The ExNulla project serves as a public demonstration of how complex technical ecosystems can
      be designed, built, and operated rapidly when architecture, automation, and AI-assisted
      workflows are aligned.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4">Contact</h2>

    <p class="text-muted">
      For interviews, collaborations, or technical discussions, contact through the links page or
      GitHub repositories associated with the project.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
